{"word":"κρείων 1","slug":"κρείων 1","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n59796\" key=\"krei/wn1\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">κρείων</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">οντος</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, <sense id=\"n59796.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">ruler, lord, master</tr_>, <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ep.\">Ep.</a></gram> </gramGrp> word, used in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> </bibl> mostly of kings and chiefs, esp. of Agamemnon, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:130\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.130</biblScope></bibl>, al. (Com. in parody, of Diomedes, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0434.tlg001:68\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Cratin.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">68</biblScope> </bibl>); of gods, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὕπατε κρειόντων</foreign>, of Zeus, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:8:31\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.31</biblScope></bibl>, etc.; of Poseidon, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">εὐρὺ κ. ἐνοσίχθων</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:11:751\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">11.751</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; as an honorary epithet, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κ. Ἐτεωνεύς</foreign>, of a squire of Menelaus, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:4:22\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.22</biblScope> </bibl>:—so fem. <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">κρείουσα</orth> (once in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl>), <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κρείουσα γυναικῶν</foreign>, of a concubine of Priam, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:22:48\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.48</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ἀντιόπη κ.</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">queen</tr_> Antiope, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0020.tlg007:110:6\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hes.\">Hes.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Fr.\">Fr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">110.6</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0533.tlg002:219\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Call.\">Call.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Del.\">Del.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">219</biblScope> </bibl>; <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Dor.\">Dor.</a></gram> </gramGrp> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">κρείοισα</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0005.tlg001.perseus-grc1:17:132\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Theoc.\">Theoc.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">17.132</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>:—after <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl> in the form <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">κρέων</orth>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg002.perseus-grc1:8:99\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pi.\">Pi.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ P.\">P.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.99</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg003.perseus-grc1:3:10\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">N.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.10</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg003.perseus-grc1:7:45\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7.45</biblScope> </bibl>; of Zeus, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0085.tlg001.perseus-grc1:574\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.\">A.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Supp.\">Supp.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">574</biblScope> </bibl> (lyr.):—fem. <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">κρέουσα</orth>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0199.tlg001:3:1\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ B.\">B.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.1</biblScope> </bibl>: hence pr. n. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Κρέων, Κρέουσα</foreign>. (A participial form (<cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">κρείειν γὰρ τὸ ἄρχειν ἔλεγον οἱ παλαιοί</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0553.tlg001:2:12\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Artem.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.12</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>): <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κρείων</foreign> may be due to metrical lengthening or represent <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Κρήων</foreign>.)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}